course_title: Diagnostics and Clinical Reasoning: Family Nurse Practitioner
course_description: This course is designed to develop assessment and clinical reasoning skills along with application and analysis of evidenced-based theory to deliver care to patients across the lifespan, promoting optimal health.
prerequisites: NRSG 544D or equivalent transfer credit as co-requisite. Students must enroll in NRSG 544D first.
